{"id": "3efc64a3-d2d6-4b05-9c37-c4c9e9fb5e39", "value": "Process whereby materials are worn away and removed by natural causes including weathering, solution, corrosion, or transportation."}

{"id": "26d7bd8b-8a4b-4daa-8b2a-093bf326432f", "value": "Constituent parts of a larger object. A component differs from an item in that the item can stand alone as an independent work but the component typically cannot or does not stand alone. Examples are a panel of a polyptych or a discrete architectural component such as a dome."}

{"id": "55915ea5-d0c5-438a-bfeb-3a979a0a2c4d", "value": "Refers to constructions of any kind artificially fabricated of parts joined together in some definite manner and which may or may not provide enclosure or shelter. Includes not just buildings, but other structures, for example oil wells, bridges, docks, and railroads. The term normally applies to structures built by humans, but may also apply to those built by other species."}
{"id": "da07c14f-0fb8-4bbc-a3ea-5f3819731604", "value": "General term for any built works or other things classified as being of the built environment, whether extant or not, constructed or not."}

{"id": "5e5e93b9-fe74-4cee-aa8c-39918277e802", "value": "Durable coverings laid down to form the surface of a road or other outdoor area; by extension, hard floor coverings in large interiors, such as public halls or churches."}

{"id": "752d5ff0-7818-4dfd-aa5a-11b87da63f1b", "value": "Landmarks, monuments, or memorials composed of stacks of stones, or burial places covered with stones or a large mound of earth. Usually reserved for ancient structures located in Scotland, Ireland, and Wales. For burial mounds specific to England, use \"barrows.\" For piles of earth, generally, use \"mounds\"; for piles of earth used specifically over tombs, use \"burial mounds.\""}
{"id": "14f2ecbd-3ffd-4566-9b5c-0cc6e98bc2ea", "value": "Aufrecht stehende Steinplatte, schmucklos oder verziert, als Gedenkstein genutzt."}
{"id": "f1242e0a-beab-4d5e-ad74-e20385c82104", "value": "Upright stone slabs, plain or decorated, used as commemorative markers."}
{"id": "1a2ec224-635d-4ded-8277-1c6eec7220e1", "value": "Objects that occur in nature, not made by humans. Used primarily in the context of distinguishing man-made objects from natural objects."}

{"id": "691c1f1d-5b36-43e4-b909-d279ff46573b", "value": "Strategically positioned architecture at the service of national defence. The structures serve the functional purpose of manning weaponry and maintaining military communication and transport routes.The shape of these buildings changes according to the military technology of a period."}
{"id": "12ed6013-358b-48bb-b12e-8cc822989fbf", "value": "Environments completely or mainly under water."}
{"id": "afe2be84-2817-413d-9d15-a0162f69b372", "value": "Umwelt, die sich zu gro\u00dfen Teilen oder vollst\u00e4ndig unter Wasser befindet."}

{"id": "0dc76625-bfab-4dbd-b2f2-2f4199517f53", "value": "Low-growing, woody perennials characterized by several branches at the base and by a lack of conspicuous trunks; generally restricted to plants under 6 m high."}
{"id": "e01730c0-14d5-4d04-83f8-f70db21a19e4", "value": "Bodies of flowing water moving in one direction, including streams and rivers."}
{"id": "6ef50902-0a4a-493f-9746-1b42660d4b0d", "value": "Frozen precipitation in the form of white or translucent hexagonal ice crystals that fall in soft, white flakes."}
{"id": "668b0c69-68ca-4f63-b5a4-c849d5bcd7df", "value": "Features comprising communities of plants that are grown by man rather than being natural."}
{"id": "46d8225b-f1df-4ea1-9f01-4c57530c91e5", "value": "Areas dominated by grasses rather than large shrubs or trees. One of the earth's six major biomes. "}
{"id": "8708a37f-7f74-4d2a-b1e7-3c7a2e306805", "value": "Gebiet, in dem Gr\u00e4ser vorherrschen statt gro\u00dfer B\u00fcsche oder B\u00e4ume. Eines der sechs gro\u00dfen Biome der Erde."}
{"id": "020504fe-0a7e-49b7-99de-956196300ecf", "value": "Extensive coverings of ice. "}
{"id": "391dc9db-382a-48cb-9a10-4c1ae1a9709f", "value": "Woody, perennial plants usually with a single, long, self-supporting stem or trunk, and which grow to a considerable height."}

{"id": "c153b32f-2fbe-4af2-aebf-638228d4b671", "value": "Siedlung jedweder Gr\u00f6\u00dfe, die nicht l\u00e4nger bewohnt wird, unabh\u00e4ngig davon, ob sie zerst\u00f6rt ist oder die Geb\u00e4ude noch intakt sind."}
{"id": "da21d410-aa0d-4b44-a805-43fc55aff560", "value": "System components that support systems of public works of countries. "}
{"id": "75e6317e-66c0-4f05-b97a-3cb8a033f66f", "value": "Settlements of any size that are no longer inhabited, whether in ruins or with intact buildings."}
{"id": "83bd18bc-5de5-4cfd-a438-b533eb9fd0eb", "value": "Presently inhabited, recently inhabited, or abandoned residences"}
{"id": "6ddd5c50-15c3-43b5-82b2-4ae3d4be1656", "value": "Refers to any abandoned settlements above ground with buildings that are partially destroyed or in ruins. "}

{"id": "88063bf9-ab00-48b1-88ac-cbf1af2716a0", "value": "Communities of any size that are the location for groups living under religious monastic order, such as monks or friars, and those who live in monasteries. "}
{"id": "576625ae-7a62-4b3c-8add-7e6817affc2f", "value": "Sites that are used for ceremonial purposes; often an ancient site, sometimes the purpose of which is unknown."}

{"id": "165b8ff4-2375-4389-97db-6fc555bdcad5", "value": "Monument for the offering of an animal, plant, or human life or of some material possession to a divinity or personage of great religious significance in order to establish, maintain, or restore a right relationship of a human being or community to the sacred order, such as through propitiation or homage."}

{"id": "e05261da-dccd-45df-b79b-6fe6737ad274", "value": "Monuments or structures built to preserve the memory of beings or events. For other objects created, issued, or worn to commemorate persons or events, use \"commemoratives.\""}
{"id": "15cb7462-2fdd-4183-a888-cef3415b9181", "value": "Objects used for a particular ritual activity, often as part of a ceremony. "}

{"id": "3f3b6ffe-e7c5-4586-a667-975a96346f5c", "value": "Piles of earth erected over grave sites; for piles of stones built over grave sites, use \"cairns\"; for piles of earth used generally and not over burials, use \"mounds.\""}

{"id": "7f361eeb-bac7-4507-a961-a382ed07d644", "value": "The area of manufacture concerned with the factors that determine where producers choose to locate and the effects of the location of a piece of land on the use made of it."}

{"id": "7eb2342a-a7b2-476d-8c84-b873c98a8c4a", "value": "A \u00e1rea de manufatura preocupada com os fatores que determinam onde os produtores escolhem se localizar e os efeitos da localiza\u00e7\u00e3o de um terreno sobre o uso que \u00e9 feito dele."}
{"id": "075a1d89-5915-4219-b327-e38ece4533fc", "value": "Ceremonial structures built for funerals or burials. "}
{"id": "8db547bd-8a6d-4aec-b6d3-687344889377", "value": "Pinturas ou esculturas trabalhavam em rochas vivas."}
{"id": "5d8b2c5f-c8d9-4899-839d-2de6bc18af5d", "value": "Paintings or carvings worked on living rock."}
{"id": "f61d888c-8e58-456b-97af-9a9007c4388b", "value": "Objects that occur in nature, not made by humans. Used primarily in the context of distinguishing man-made objects from natural objects."}

{"id": "7d8f07ac-ba62-49fa-92c9-78826d96707c", "value": "The purpose or activity realized by a thing, the way in which a thing operates or the objective for which it is used. May be applied to people, other beings, or institutions as well."}

{"id": "d3b9e295-861c-45ec-846c-337ea87bde4c", "value": "Materials produced by weaving, felting, knotting, twining, or otherwise processing natural or synthetic fibers so that they cohere into a form or unit; traditionally excludes fiberboard, paper, papier-m\u00e2ch\u00e9, and papyrus, which, though also fiber products, are considered as separate types of material. For generic reference to the genre, see \"textiles.\""}
{"id": "49c57879-3c5b-48f9-ae10-ee53f45d2fee", "value": "In archaeology, describes prehistoric chipped-stone artifacts and debitage."}
{"id": "f631659c-a05c-42d6-a669-6139736ce133", "value": "The body or bodies of a deceased person or people, in whole or in parts, regardless of the stage of decomposition or preservation."}

{"id": "27455e3a-a5cc-4dc3-96ca-0c8928074e45", "value": "Der K\u00f6rper oder die K\u00f6rper einer verstorbenen Person oder eines Volkes im Ganzen oder in Teilen, unabh\u00e4ngig vom Erhaltungszustand."}

{"id": "5915c656-1477-4b14-8c42-c63f47fa1959", "value": "Object genre including visual works and other articles made of ceramic, which is any of various hard, brittle, heat-resistant and corrosion-resistant materials made by shaping and then firing a nonmetallic mineral, such as clay, at a high temperature. Ceramic ware, earthenware, porcelain ware, and brick products are examples of ceramics."}

{"id": "6eb91fbe-7412-4fb0-893f-0b9236498f91", "value": "Objects and other material culture found in contexts of archaeological research, typically reserved for those unearthed from periods before usually the 19th century and from extinct cultures. For objects originating in any culture still living or known through relatively recent history when those articles are the concern of ethnographic or ethnological study, prefer \"ethnographic objects.\""}

{"id": "5ec2dc9a-d67d-4418-aff5-f5fdb6a99309", "value": "Im Zusammenhang mit arch\u00e4ologischen Untersuchungen gefundenes Objekt, pr\u00e4ziser: Objekt einer Ausgrabung, gew\u00f6hnlich aus Zeitr\u00e4umen vor dem 19. Jahrundert, nicht mehr existierenden Kulturen zugeordnet. F\u00fcr Objekte aus gegenw\u00e4rtigen oder erst k\u00fcrzlich verschwundenen Kulturen ist bei ethnografischem oder ethnologischem Wert \"Ethnografisches Objekt\" zu verwenden. "}

{"id": "4155d9ad-3495-4bc4-a09e-69a150f23857", "value": "A sample is a part of anything taken or presented for inspection or shown as evidence of the quality or composition of the whole. For instances that represent a class, use \"specimens.\""}
{"id": "27811c96-8d45-41a1-a298-f36527eaf6e3", "value": "Refers to all of the animals or animal life of a particular area or time period."}

{"id": "6c0b31ee-680e-4e2c-b52e-1f2a15ed52b4", "value": "Process or action of digging to extract metal, coal, or other substances, or to create a tunnel, such as under a wall, fort, mountain, or another thing."}
{"id": "736b1ce6-e54f-4c87-a471-62eeea04a981", "value": "Any place where burials have taken place, generally restricted to human or other hominin burials."}

{"id": "40c30d6b-c7c6-4e12-9277-12b8c15671ce", "value": "Gro\u00dfformatiges, flach reliefiertes, gemei\u00dfeltes, geritztes oder gemaltes Bild auf anstehendem Fels, oft von fr\u00fchen Kulturen geschaffen."}

{"id": "59a9e97b-d8fe-42b7-b4dc-3195624afe89", "value": "Manufactories that specialize in creating articles made of ceramic, which is a hard, brittle, heat-resistant and corrosion-resistant material, including earthenware, porcelain, and brick."}
{"id": "5eb2e5ba-58e1-4fc2-9050-73c04a1476e8", "value": "Melting or fusing ore, often with an accompanying chemical change, usually to separate the metal."}
{"id": "39483c7d-5192-47ee-83a3-408dc0fec5e3", "value": "Pinturas feitas em rochas localizadas em seu ambiente original, geralmente por povos antigos."}
{"id": "1c600884-55d9-40b0-b5ac-eeaa5d65259f", "value": "Paintings made on living rock, usually by ancient peoples."}

{"id": "9a0a70a1-ecb3-4be8-886e-f1fb7efff898", "value": "Rooms or other areas, above or below ground, that are reserved for burial, generally intended to accomodate one or a small number of bodies."}
{"id": "26583b30-fbd5-4940-8117-888b378d2361", "value": "General functions and processes that occur in agriculture. "}
